Democratic caucus stopped short of ushering <strong>Alexandria Ocasio-Corte=
z</strong> into leadership. For the past several weeks, House minority lead=
er <strong>Hakeem Jeffries</strong> stood back and allowed junior members t=
o challenge the old guard for senior committee assignments. Alas, A.O.C., w=
